cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the training of algorithms for prosthetic control. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on improving the intuitive control of prostheses. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses supervised learning of neural or myoelectric prosthetic control. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of biological recordings to correlate with motor intent. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper uses an infrared camera to track hand joint angles in real-time.
